President Barack Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. These appointments include Anita Fineday and Russ McDonald as members of the Alyce Spotted Bear and Walter Soboleff Commission on Native Children, Valerie Jarrett and Susan Rice as General Trustees of the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, Linda Smith as a member of the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences, Carole Johnson as a member of the National Cancer Advisory Board, and various individuals as members of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition, President's National Security Telecommunications Advisory Committee, Roosevelt Campobello International Park Commission, United States Holocaust Memorial Council, Western Hemisphere Drug Policy Commission, J. William Fulbright Foreign Scholarship Board, and more. President Obama expressed confidence that these appointees would serve the American people well.